rComments: He made the asynchronous course feel like I wasn't just staring at a pre recorded video. I love that he added himself in a box in the corner. It was very engaging. Study hard and you'll do amazing. Just don't skip out on his lectures, he explains topics much better than the readings. So read the readings as enrichment sources.

Professor Copeland was good. When I watched his lecture videos, he explained circulatory system very thoroughly. There is a lot of textbook readings in ANP1105 so do not be behind those readings. Many questions on the final and midterms are from textbooks. His email replies are direct and informative. Good luck!
Anatomy is a hard class but if you're taking it online it's definitely not too overwhelming. Classes were asynchronous with the lecture recordings being very nicely organized
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: If you actually study the material you will get a great mark. His tests were extremely fair. Also tried to make a couple jokes which was nice when watching a recorded lecture.

Copeland was probably one of the better anatomy profs that I had. His lectures were fairly short which I loved (around 20 mins when other profs gave 1 hr and 20 min lectures). His exams were really fair and honestly easy. I would definitely take him again. My respect for him skyrocketed after I experienced prof fortier.

He's really not as bad as everyone makes him to be. For me, he meets the average he does prepare his lecture slides in bulk, but that's so you don't have to keep printing slides every time & he takes a few classes to go over all of them. Lectures are fairly short, but I like taking supplementary notes.

Really passionate about the course, and he does his best to respond to any question the best way he can. He posts prerecorded lectures so you can watch them on your own time, and every lecture is a maximum 35min which makes focusing and paying attention easier.

Had a little video of him talking in the side of the powerpoint which honestly made the lectures so much easier to watch rather than just the audio clips attached. Split the class with Staines, learned more from Copeland but was glad they were together. Midterms and finals were fair, and open book. Good class!

John is fantastic. He is very professional and passionate. He tries to interact and use objects to engage the students. I loved John a lot and I recommend him highly. The class is very difficult. I had William along with John and WIlliam was god awful. Nobody could learn from him. SO if you have both of them, drop if or try to switch.

Honestly no where near as bad as people make him out to be. I dont have much to say about him as a lecturer (only attended 1 class), but it isnt hard to get an A+ if you thoroughly study the textbook. He recycled 90% of his old exam on the midterm. He doesnt add anything new to his powerpoint, so attendance isnt necessary.

Had him for the Fall 2018 semester, not a great prof since he pretty much just reads what's on the slides at a very quick pace and writing notes during class is pretty useless. I realized in ANP1106 the following semester that the trick is to just study the textbook throughout the semester cause Copeland might as well not be there during lectures.
Slideshows he used weren't his own, so he didn't explain them well. Mumbled a lot. Exams were very difficult. One of two professors teaching the course, and definitely the worse of the two.
Want to pass memorize everything. Prof is ok. I suggest you study cause nothing is really taught
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Exam material didn't reflect stuff taught in class, and gave us no idea what to expect in exams. Most material came from book but even then some test material was never taught. He expects you to basically memorize every single thing since most of the exam questions were on very small details and not the stuff that he spends most of his time on.

A solid prof. Course requires a lot of memory; wish the prof gave more ideas what to study. The final had too much material to study especially when you have heavy courses. Hes a very good prof just ready and memorize:

Explains concepts clearly and passionately with many real-life examples. Lecture slides contained only brief information. Assignments are extremely easy. Studied first two midterms for less than a week from textbook, and still got a very decent mark. But barely passed final because too much material, so keep studying consistently.
Stop using up valuable class time to discuss your research.

Really good lecturer and very clear. Kinda know him on a personal level as he goes to my gym and i would often ask him questions after class. For him you should try to take notes (unlike staines) but only brief notes not everything he says and rely mostly on the text. Its a course you can't just do the week before and get a good grade; work hard.
Explains concepts well and seems to be passionate about the subject matter. He let us know the main concepts to study for midterms/exams and is a pretty easy going prof.

He makes things really clear. I didn't understand a lot of the information from another professor teaching the course, but Copeland gives really good examples and makes the information clear and interesting! He also clearly maps out what we need to and don't need to know for the exam. Like him!

His slides are brief details, so reading the textbook is a must. He does go off topic many times and incorporates his findings from his studies with specific subjects which is not needed since it is not what we are talking about. His midterms are somewhat decent. Reading the textbook is a must. Study!
Decent professor, midterms were fair and slideshows were informative
Good prof. Doesn't know a lot of the answers to questions asked in class. Questions asked on the midterm and final were fair. Lecture information is directly from the textbook

Lecture notes are great, pulled right from the textbook so they don't miss a detail... THEREFORE, attendance wasn't necessary. He is very nice though! Midterm and final were very fair, no trick questions if you study and know your stuff.
Good guy. Keeps things real, likable guy, you dont get mad at him when hes teaching or taking questions. Good teaching but do your work prior. Like him a lot.

Very hard to understand and mumbles quite frequently. Also he doesn't know the answers to the majority of questions, and avoids answering questions by answering a question that he does know the answer to.
Only prof teaching this course that could be understood. Easy midterm questions as well.
He is an excellent professor. He makes the class interesting because he actually seems to care about what he's talking about!Love him!
